cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for visual tracking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes two regression models, which involve the use of neural networks and kernelized ridge regression, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in multimedia processing, suggesting that it could also belong to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's focus on visual tracking suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
